<FIRST>r i AM-Italy-PLO     02-12 0161</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Italy-PLO,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thousands in Rome Express Support for Palestinian State</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 30,000 Italian and Arab demonstrators waving
banners and chanting slogans marched Saturday to support creation of
a Palestinian state, Italian news agencies said.
   The agencies said the march, organized by the Italian League for
People's Rights and the Association for Peace, was led by students
waving the Palestinian flag and holding portraits of Palestine
Liberation Organization chairman Yasser Arafat.
   The demonstrators gathered outside the basilica of St. John the
Lateran to hear a speech by Nemer Hammad, the PLO representative in
Italy.
   ``We want Palestine to return to being the land of peace,''
Hammad told the demonstrators.
   The 14-month-old Palestinian uprising in the Israeli-occupied
West Bank and Gaza Strip has left at least 380 Palestinians and 15
Israelis dead.
   Near the end of the peaceful demonstration a group of about a
hundred protestors burned an Israeli flag and called for armed
struggle in the occupied territories.
</TEXT>
