<FIRST>r a AM-Marine-Spy     02-12 0341</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Marine-Spy,0351</SECOND>
<HEAD>Report: Feds Still Convinced Ex-Marine Was Spy; Man Says No</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former U.S. Marine says he was coerced into
signing a confession admitting he was a spy, but the government
maintains that Arnold Bracy is a liar who gave away secrets for sex
while in Moscow, CBS News reports.
   In an interview to be aired Sunday on the network's ``60
Minutes'' program, Bracy, of New York, told correspondent Mike
Wallace that he was forced to sign a confession and that Naval
investigators knew it was false.
   ``As I said, the things that they put in that statement that they
accused me of doing I know never happened,'' Bracy said.
   The government had just uncovered a spy for sex scandal in Moscow
in 1987 when Bracy was interrogated. In the confession, which he
later recanted, he admitted a sexual relationship with a Russian
cook at the U.S. Embassy in Moscow. He also confessed to allowing
KGB agents roam in the U.S. Embassy.
   In the CBS interview, Bracy denied that he slept with the Russian
woman and said he never allowed KGB agents into the embassy. Bracy
at one time faced a military court-martial but all charges were
dropped when military lawyers concluded they did not have any
corroborating evidence to prosecute.
   He was discharged from the Marines last spring.
   Ron Kessler, a former Washington Post reporter and the author of
a new book on the Moscow spy scandal, also was interviewed by
Wallace.
   Kessler said Bracy allowed KGB agents into the embassy's computer
nerve-center where they planted electronic listening devices. As a
result, Kessler contends that 25 Soviet citizens who worked for the
CIA were exposed and later executed.
   Bracy denied the charge, saying he did not have access to the
computer room.
   But Jim Pender, a Naval Investigative Service agent who
interrogated Bracy, told CBS he is convinced that Bracy was a spy
for the Soviets while stationed in Moscow.
   ``It's my feeling that Bracy has been a liar all his life,''
Pender said.
</TEXT>
