<FIRST>r i AM-Algeria-Quakes     02-12 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Algeria-Quakes,0126</SECOND>
<HEAD>Earthquakes Recorded in Algeria</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALGIERS, Algeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two earthquakes struck Algeria on Sunday,
but there were no reports of damage or injuries, officials said.
   The first quake hit an area about 30 miles east of Algiers and
measured 4.9 on the Richter scale, according to the National
Astronomy and Geophysics Center.
   A quake measuring about 3 on the scale was felt a little later in
Batna, a region in far eastern Algeria, the center reported.
   The Richter scale is a measure of energy released by an
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a
seismograph. A quake with a magnitude of 4 has the potential to
cause moderate damage, while one measuring 5 can cause considerable
damage.
