<SECOND>AM-Fire Deaths,0354</SECOND>
<HEAD>Trucks Ran Out Of Water Fighting Fire That Killed Eight</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUGUSTA, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Volunteer firemen ran out of water fighting
a house fire that killed eight people, and had to refill the water
tanks on their trucks five miles away, authorities said.
   But officials said the fire spread so fast that more water
probably would not have saved the lives of the eight family members
who died in the blaze early Saturday.
   ``I don't think water would have made much of a difference as far
as lives,'' said Deputy Forrest Brewster of the sheriff's office.
   ``The roof had already caved in when I got there at 3:40 a.m.,''
Brewster said. ``It was engulfed in flames. There wasn't any sounds
coming from inside there then.''
   J.B. Gibbs, who is in his 50s, and his daughter Angela, in her
20s, escaped. His wife, six of their children and a 2-year-old
granddaughter were found dead in their beds in two bedrooms _ five
in one and three in the other.
   Gibbs was awakened by the fire and tried to wake his wife,
Bernice, ``but she wouldn't move,'' said Woodruff County Sheriff
Leon Creasey.
   ``He was hysterical,'' the sheriff said.
   The fire, which authorities believe started from a crack in the
chimney attached to a wood-burning stove used to heat the house, was
reported by neighbors just after 3 a.m..
   Brewster said the four 500-gallon trucks from three volunteer
fire departments responding to the blaze made five or more trips to
fire hydrants in the Grays community, five miles away, to fill up
their tanks.
   The home in Revels, about 60 miles northeast of Little Rock, was
due to be connected to the public water supply in the spring, but
was still relying on well water along with other homes in the rural
community, according to Woodruff County Judge John Davis.
   Creasey identified the dead members of the Gibbs' family as
Bernice, 46; Audrey, 25; Shirley, 30; Kartarla, 18; Belisha 14;
John, 15; J.B., 22; and Cortney Gibbs, 2, daughter of Audrey Gibbs.
